column8: >The Riedell 3030 Aria is a sleek, strong, and lightweight boot, with the advantages of leather materials that mold to the skater’s foot, providing an exceptionally perfect fit.

column6: >Designed for top competitors, the <strong style=""line-height: inherit
column7: >Riedell Aria is for high-level skaters looking for ultimate performance and the best possible ergonomics and fit.

column6: >Inside the Aria, quadruple-layer reinforcements provide our firmest support and are heat moldable for the perfect fit. The extra firm support is balanced with the comfort of a luxuriously smooth antimicrobial leather lining that wicks moisture. Aria's taller toe box and an internal forefoot relief increase foot comfort on landings.

>Our innovative leather/cork heel and water-resistant ultra-thin outsole provide weight reduction, optimal support, and impact absorption. Aria's one-of-a-kind internal midsole technology further reduces weight and keeps you closer to the ice for added control.

>The winning balance of long-lasting comfort and support in the Aria skating boot is a choice for most demanding skaters, such as 2-time World Champion Stephane Lambiel and World Medalist Vincent Zhou.

column2:
>Powerdyne Arius Platinum Plate:

The newest Arius Platinum plate from Powerdyne is a totally new design plate with no more traditional kingpin.
The Arius features the progressive lateral movement which creates efficient pressure while eliminating traditional stress points that cause breakage.

The Arius is a 6061 series heat treated lightweight extruded aircraft aluminum plate with an anodized metallic red finishing.

Precision machined aluminum trucks with chromoly steal axles.

The Powerdyne Arius Platinum also features the Unique Butterfly cushion design which requires no adjustment.

4 sets of high rebound urethane butterfly cushions come with the Arius plate.

The Arius is now available at our store in Miami.

column2: >The New Riedell R3 derby is the perfect skate to start derby skating,
>There is no better option in the entry level class than the Riedell R3 Derby Roller Skate Set.

column1: A favorite with skaters since it debuted, the R3 boot features class-leading build quality
including a special grade of vinyl that is more durable than standard vinyl and a detailed
boot construction process that was developed from our decades of boot-making experience.
Derby is a demanding sport though, so to ready the R3 for derby use, we added black
tough scuff leather toe caps to prevent abrasion, reinforced PowerDyne Thrust nylon plates
for a firm base, and Sonar Striker wheels that grip on all kinds of surfaces.

column2: >The New Riedell R3 derby features the new Sonar Striker wheels

column1: and a leather Toe Cap.

column1:

for a firm base\, and Sonar Striker wheels that grip on all kinds of surfaces.

column1: The 3200 roller skate boot provides the stiffness and supports you need to be at the top of your shuffle skate game.
The Riedell 3200 features full-grain leather uppers and a soft Strata microfiber lining with moisture and odor-resistant treatment.
Cushy premium foam lines the tongue and the contoured collar, making for an ultra-comfortable fit.
Unique to the 3200 in our line is the ForeFlex design that enhances the fit and flexes for the small toe and ball area of the boot.
Finally, lightweight cork heels provide incredible shock absorption, and extra firm quarter panels offer support for advanced dance skate moves.

33366,simple,RollLine7mmAxlelocknutsGold,,Roll-line 7 mm Axle Locknuts Gold,1,0,visible,"

Roll-Line 7mm Axle Locknuts Gold - Secure and Stylish

\nIntroducing the Roll-Line 7mm Axle Locknuts Gold, an essential accessory for your roller skates. These high-quality skate accessories come in a pack of 8 and feature a stylish gold (brass plated) finish. Designed to provide secure fastening and long-lasting durability, these locknuts are perfect for maintaining your skates and ensuring a smooth ride. Upgrade your skating gear with the best Roll-Line axle locknuts.","

Enhance Your Skating Experience with Roll-Line 7mm Axle Locknuts Gold

\nThe Roll-Line 7mm Axle Locknuts Gold are a crucial component for any skater looking to maintain their equipment at the highest level. These locknuts are designed to secure your axles firmly, ensuring safety and performance during your skating sessions. With a stylish gold (brass plated) finish, they not only offer functionality but also add a touch of elegance to your skates.

\nChoosing the Roll-Line 7mm Axle Locknuts means opting for premium quality and reliability. These locknuts are recommended to be changed after about six removals or if they can be turned with fingers, as worn-out nylon inserts may not stay securely in place. The Roll-Line company emphasizes the importance of maintaining your locknuts to ensure optimal performance and safety.

\nHistorically, roller skates used jam nuts instead of the nylon-inserted locknuts used today. Jam nuts had to be locked down completely to prevent loosening, requiring perfect alignment of spacers and bearings. Today, the use of nylon-inserted locknuts simplifies maintenance while ensuring secure fastening. The Roll-Line locknuts are designed to meet modern standards, providing a secure and reliable solution for your skating needs.

\n
  • High-Quality Construction: Made from durable materials with a brass-plated gold finish.

\n
  • Secure Fastening: Ensures your axles remain firmly in place during use.

\n
  • Easy Maintenance: Recommended to be replaced after about six removals or if they loosen easily.

\n
  • Pack Size: Comes in a pack of 8 for comprehensive maintenance.

\n
  • Compatibility: Suitable for various types of roller skates and skateboards.

\nUsing the Roll-Line 7mm Axle Locknuts Gold, you can ensure your skates are always in top condition. These locknuts provide a secure fit, reducing the risk of axle loosening and enhancing your overall skating experience. Regularly replacing your locknuts is essential for maintaining the performance and safety of your skates.

\nThe Roll-Line locknuts are designed with precision and quality in mind, making them a reliable choice for skaters who demand the best. Whether you're a professional skater or a recreational enthusiast, these locknuts will help you keep your skates performing at their best. Upgrade your skate maintenance routine with the best skate accessories from Roll-Line.",,,taxable,,1,,,0,0,0.15,,,,0,,,17.0,"Roller Skates > Roll Line Skates > Roll Line Accessories, Roller Skates > Roll Line Skates > Roll Line Skate Parts, Roller Skates > Roll Line Skates",,,http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/7mm-Axle-Locknuts-GOLD.jpeg,,,,,RollLine7mmAxlelocknutsGold,,,,0,Roll Line,,,ExtraField 1,Roll-Line 7mm Axle locknuts Gold,1.0,0.0,ExtraField 6,"Roll Line Axle Locnuts 7mm GOLD

The Roll line company always recommends changing LockNuts after about 6 times of removal
or especially if you can turn them with your fingers.

When the NYLON insert wears out they will not stay in position unless locked completely down like the older style Jam Nuts.

If you look at the roller skating history years ago\, when we used Jam Nuts instead of the Nylon inserted Lock Nuts used today.
A Jam Nut must be locked down to keep from loosening and coming off.
To achieve good Roll from this type of configuration\, the sides of the spacer must be absolutely parallel\, without any burrs and just
a couple of thousandths of an inch wider than the web (that smaller center portion) of the wheel or space between the Bearings.
The sizes of the web of the Wheels vary between manufacturers and even between various wheels from the same manufacturer\, in some cases.

Many years ago\, the wheel manufacturers used to supply the Spacers with the Wheels.
When the Axle Nut is tightened down on the wheel (with bearings and a spacer)\, it creates a solid boss of material
(the inner race of the inside Bearing\, the Spacer\, and the inner race of the outside Bearing)
that effectively increases the Axle size from 7mm to approximately 14mm.
The increasing of the Axle size greatly reduces the possibility of bending or breaking any Axle.
By locking the Bearings and Spacer down\, it also assures that the center race of each Bearing is not spinning on the Axle\,
but that the balls of the Bearings are actually doing the work that they are intended to.
Tightening the Axle Nut on a Wheel without a Spacer can severely mis-align the center races of the bearings to the outer races
of the Bearings by compressing the inner races towards the center of the Wheel.
The Locked Down approach also requires near perfect alignment of the Wheel bore and the web of the Wheel must have very
clean square corners to provide a seat for the outer race of the Bearings.

Today\, Lock Nuts are accepted\, most Wheel manufacturers do not even supply the Wheel Spacers\, and the tolerances on the width
of the web of the Wheel are not held as tight as they once were.
To my knowledge\, Roll-Line is the only one still making Spacers for Wheels.
They normally come with a complete NEW Frame as an accessory.
Rollerskateusa.com does have spacers available in sets of 8 from Roll-Line.
(Just a Note: not every spacer will make every wheel work properly. Sometimes there are spacers that are non-parallel\,
have a burr\, or are just too small to match the web of a specific Wheel.)

The spacers have always been a part that the manufacturing cost must be minimized\, or for some manufacturers\, completely eliminated.
They are made from a long tube that is sawn into the Spacers\, and the tolerances are not usually as rigorously controlled as on other parts
of the Skate. To get the Spacers\, Bearings and Wheels to work\, means sometimes using multiple Spacers to get a specific wheel to roll properly.

When everything goes together well\, there should be little to no variation in the speed of a free spinning Wheel
(with the Axle Nut (Lock Nut) is just backed off) and when the Axle Nut (Lock Nut) is tightened down.

To achieve a Free Rolling complete set of Wheels in this manner will take time and patience and plenty of Spacers along with a good Bearing Press
like the our new Roll-Line Bearing Press/Puller.

\nThe Roll-Line locknuts are designed with precision and quality in mind, making them a reliable choice for skaters who demand the best. Whether you're a professional skater or a recreational enthusiast, these locknuts will help you keep your skates performing at their best. Upgrade your skate maintenance routine with the best skate accessories from Roll-Line.",,,taxable,,1,,,0,0,0.15,9,6.0,2.0,0,,,12.0,"Roller Skates > Roll Line Skates > Roll Line Accessories, Roller Skates > Roll Line Skates > Roll Line Skate Parts, Roller Skates > Roll Line Skates",,,http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/RollLine7mmAxlelocknutsSilver2.jpg,,,,,RollLine7mmAxlelocknutsSilver,,,,0,Roll Line,,,ExtraField 1,Roll-Line 7mm Axle locknuts,1.0,0.0,ExtraField 6,"Roll Line Axle Locnuts 7mm Silver

The Roll line company always recommends changing LockNuts after about 6 times of removal
or especially if you can turn them with your fingers.

When the NYLON insert wears out they will not stay in position unless locked completely down like the older style Jam Nuts.

If you look at the roller skating history years ago\, when we used Jam Nuts instead of the Nylon inserted Lock Nuts used today.
A Jam Nut must be locked down to keep from loosening and coming off.
To achieve good Roll from this type of configuration\, the sides of the spacer must be absolutely parallel\, without any burrs and just
a couple of thousandths of an inch wider than the web (that smaller center portion) of the wheel or space between the Bearings.
The sizes of the web of the Wheels vary between manufacturers and even between various wheels from the same manufacturer\, in some cases.

Many years ago\, the wheel manufacturers used to supply the Spacers with the Wheels.
When the Axle Nut is tightened down on the wheel (with bearings and a spacer)\, it creates a solid boss of material
(the inner race of the inside Bearing\, the Spacer\, and the inner race of the outside Bearing)
that effectively increases the Axle size from 7mm to approximately 14mm.
The increasing of the Axle size greatly reduces the possibility of bending or breaking any Axle.
By locking the Bearings and Spacer down\, it also assures that the center race of each Bearing is not spinning on the Axle\,
but that the balls of the Bearings are actually doing the work that they are intended to.
Tightening the Axle Nut on a Wheel without a Spacer can severely mis-align the center races of the bearings to the outer races
of the Bearings by compressing the inner races towards the center of the Wheel.
The Locked Down approach also requires near perfect alignment of the Wheel bore and the web of the Wheel must have very
clean square corners to provide a seat for the outer race of the Bearings.

Today\, Lock Nuts are accepted\, most Wheel manufacturers do not even supply the Wheel Spacers\, and the tolerances on the width
of the web of the Wheel are not held as tight as they once were.
To my knowledge\, Roll-Line is the only one still making Spacers for Wheels.
They normally come with a complete NEW Frame as an accessory.
Rollerskateusa.com does have spacers available in sets of 8 from Roll-Line.
(Just a Note: not every spacer will make every wheel work properly. Sometimes there are spacers that are non-parallel\,
have a burr\, or are just too small to match the web of a specific Wheel.)

The spacers have always been a part that the manufacturing cost must be minimized\, or for some manufacturers\, completely eliminated.
They are made from a long tube that is sawn into the Spacers\, and the tolerances are not usually as rigorously controlled as on other parts
of the Skate. To get the Spacers\, Bearings and Wheels to work\, means sometimes using multiple Spacers to get a specific wheel to roll properly.

When everything goes together well\, there should be little to no variation in the speed of a free spinning Wheel
(with the Axle Nut (Lock Nut) is just backed off) and when the Axle Nut (Lock Nut) is tightened down.

To achieve a Free Rolling complete set of Wheels in this manner will take time and patience and plenty of Spacers along with a good Bearing Press
like the our new Roll-Line Bearing Press/Puller.

\nThe Roll-Line Action Adjustments Nuts for click action are designed to provide skaters with precise control and superior durability. Also known as Click Nuts, these adjustment nuts are crafted with a lightweight and strong construction, making them an essential accessory for any serious skater. Upgrade your skate setup with these premium roller skate accessories from Roll-Line.

\nChoosing the Roll-Line Action Adjustments Nuts for click action mean opting for enhanced performance and reliability. These nuts are specifically designed to offer a secure and precise fit, ensuring that your skates perform at their best. \n
  • Lightweight and Strong: Constructed for durability and ease of use.

\n
  • Precision Fit: Machined divots ensure a secure lock into the suspension click action cups.

\n

\nWith the Roll-Line Action Adjustment Nuts for Click Action, you can ensure that your skates are fine-tuned to perfection. These adjustment nuts are designed to provide the stability and precision you need for top performance. Whether you're adjusting your skates for a competition or everyday use, these nuts will provide the reliable action you need.

\nUpgrade your skate maintenance routine with the best skate accessories from Roll-Line. These adjustment nuts are engineered for excellence, ensuring that you enjoy a superior skating experience every time. Don't settle for less—choose Roll-Line Action Adjustments Nuts for Click Action for unmatched performance and reliability.",,,taxable,,1,,,0,0,0.15,,,,0,,,30.0,"Roller Skates > Roll Line Skates > Roll Line Accessories, Roller Skates > Roll Line Skates > Roll Line Skate Parts, Roller Skates > Roll Line Skates",,,http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/rolllineactionadjnutforclicka2.jpeg,,,,,RollLineAction-AdjNutforClickA,,,,0,Roll Line,,,ExtraField 1,Roll-Line Lower Suspension Click Action Cups,1.0,0.0,ExtraField 6,"

column3:
>Roll-Line Adjustment â€œClick-Actionâ€ Nuts or also called â€œClick Nutsâ€ are engineered to be light-weight and withstand the use
and abuse of high level competitive Skating.

Roll-Line Adjustment â€œClick-Actionâ€ Nuts or also called â€œClick Nutsâ€ are closest to the Skating Surface.
These specially machined Brass Nuts are the same for ALL Roll-Line â€œClick-Actionâ€ Skate Frames.

The back side surface of the â€œClick Nutâ€ has machined divots that lock into the Lower Suspension (Cushion) â€œClick-Actionâ€ Cups
or â€œClick Capsâ€.

The â€œClick Nutâ€ adjusts the tension desired on the Suspensions (Cushions).
Left to Loosen
Right to Tighten
When looking from the bottom of the Skate Frame.
This adjustment is made with the 17mm end of the Tube Wrench.

In most cases\, when setting up the Skate Tension Adjustments for the first time\, it is a good idea to loosen up the â€œClick Nutsâ€
all the way for all four (4) trucks.

This will allow you to count the â€œClicksâ€ and bring all four (4) trucks up to the same tension. It is also recommended to make the
Back Trucks (on each foot)\, one (1) â€œClickâ€ Looser than the Front Trucks.

This will allow for easier steering when Skating Backwards.

If the â€œClick Nutâ€ is loosened to the point that it hits and is pushing on the Adjustment King Pin Locking Screw (the Keeper Screw)\,
and more Action (flexibility) is desired in the Suspensions (Cushions)\, then a softer Suspension may be needed.

    • The Roll-Line Carbon J ABEC 5 Bearings are specifically made for very High Level Competitive Roller Skating.
    The Carbon J Bearings are Free Rolling with minimal Radial Play which promotes and very evenly distributes the load across
    the 7 balls for optimal Roll and a good amount of Axial Play or Thrust\, which is the side movement of the inner race in relation to the outer race.
    This movement is very important because when Skaters push\, we always put side load on the skate to get power in the push or stroke.
    If the Bearing does not allow for this\, it will bind and Loose operating speed or Roll.

    These provisions in the Race Curvature and Contact Angle allow the Roll-Line Carbon J Bearings to Roll freely.

    The Roll-Line Carbon J Abec 5 Bearings is ONLY available for Skates with 7mm Axles.

column2:
>Roll Line Speed Max Abec 9 Bearings

The Roll-Line Speed Max Professional Bearings are specifically designed and manufactured for very High Level Competitive Roller Skating of all types.

The Roll-Line Speed Max is a copy of the original Snyder Super Fafnir Bearings which sold for $160.00 per set in 1982 when they were released.
The Roll-Line Speed Max bearings carry all of the hallmarks and performance of the original Bearings\, with a couple of upgrades that were not available in 1982.

We consider the Speed Max to be the Best Skating Bearings available at any cost.

The Roll Line Speed Max Professional Bearings are Free Rolling with minimal Radial Play which promotes and very evenly distributes the load across the 8 balls
for optimal Roll and a good amount of Axial Play or Thrust\, which is the side movement of the inner race in relation to the outer race.

This movement is very important because when Skaters push\, we always put side load on the skate to get power in the push or stroke.
If the Bearing does not allow for this\, it will bind and Loose operating speed or Roll.

These provisions in the Race Curvature and Contact Angle allow the Roll-Line Speed Max Bearings to Roll very freely.

The Roll-Line Speed Max have a single metal Shield to help keep the dust and dirt out.
The Speed Max has a high performance Ball Crown Cage is Carbon impregnated to provide a little extra dry lubrication to ensure these Bearings
will perform far beyond most other Bearings.

The Roll-Line Speed Max Bearings are available for Skates with 7mm.
The resiliency and strength of Bearings with 8 Steel Balls provide better performance for much less cost than other bearings on the market.
Many World level Skaters and Champions in Artistic and Quad Ball Hockey have been using the Speed Max for many years.

column3:
>Roll Line Helium outdoor wheels :


The new Roll Line Helium Jam Wheels are the result of a long term research project which has produced very High Performance Indoor/Outdoor wheels.

The Rollline Helium Wheels are specifically designed for Roller Derby and Jam Skating\, where Hi-Rebound and Good Roll are needed in combination with incredibly Tight Grip. (High Rebound means the wheels can roll over some small obstacles or rocks without stopping cold.) What a smooth ride! Roll-Line has developed this wheel giving it properties that are normally not achievable in the one wheel\, Super Tight Grip and Good Roll. Roll-Line based the design of the wheel on a Large Rigid Hub and a Smaller\, Thinner Tread\, and produced one of the TIGHTEST\, and Good ROLLING Indoor/Outdoor wheels available.

The Roll-Line company has developed the Hub which is incredibly Strong\, very Light.
column4:
>The Roll-Line HELIUM Tread is a Cast Urethane Hi-Rebound Compound Formula\, which is just a small amount harder than the HYDROGEN\, yet it provides a very Tight Grip\, with a minimum of tire compression that is normally associated with a wheel this tight.

The lack of tire compression\, along with the thinner tread\, mounted on the Roll-Line Hub\, is what provides the very Good SMOOTH Roll.

Upgrade Your Skates with Roll-Line Lower Suspension Cushion Click Action Cups

\nThe Roll-Line Lower Suspension Cushion Click Action Cups are designed to provide top-notch performance and durability for skaters. These click action cups, also known as click caps, are lightweight yet extremely strong, ensuring your skates perform at their best.

\n

\nChoosing the Roll-Line Lower Suspension Cushion Click Action Cups means opting for superior quality and reliability. Roll-Line Variant C FreeStyle/Dance Roller Skate Plate

\nThe Roll-Line Variant C Roller Skate Plate represents the latest in roller skate technology, featuring an innovative Click Action adjustment system. This advanced system allows for precise and easy adjustments, providing skaters with enhanced control and performance. The plate is crafted from aircraft aluminum steel alloy, ensuring durability and a lightweight design that offers superior support.

\nThe Variant C plate includes aircraft aluminum trucks equipped with 7mm steel axles and adjustable pivot pins. These components work together to deliver exceptional stability and responsiveness, making it ideal for various skating disciplines. The professional natural rubber suspensions provide excellent cushioning, reducing vibrations and enhancing comfort during skating sessions. Additionally, the professional white metric toe stop (not canted) ensures reliable braking power for quick stops and precise control.

\nWhether you are into freestyle, derby, hockey, dance, figure, rhythm, or jam skating, the Roll-Line Variant C plate is designed to meet your needs and help you achieve your best performance. Please note that 7mm wheel spacers and mounting hardware are not included.","

Roll-Line Variant C FreeStyle/Dance Roller Skate Plate

\nThe Roll-Line Variant C Roller Skate Plate is a cutting-edge product designed for skaters who demand precision and performance. This plate features the latest Click Action adjustment system, which allows for quick and easy adjustments, ensuring your skates are always perfectly tuned to your preferences. Made from high-quality aircraft aluminum steel alloy, the Variant C plate is both lightweight and incredibly durable, providing the support you need for advanced skating.

\nThe standout feature of the Variant C plate is its Click Action adjustment system. This innovative system simplifies the process of making fine-tuned adjustments, enabling skaters to achieve optimal performance with minimal effort. Whether you are performing intricate dance routines or navigating through a high-intensity derby bout, the Click Action system ensures your skates respond accurately to every movement.

\nThe aircraft aluminum trucks are equipped with 7mm steel axles and adjustable pivot pins, offering robust support and flexibility. This combination of materials and design ensures that the Variant C plate can withstand the demands of competitive skating while providing a smooth and responsive experience. The adjustable pivot pins allow you to customize your setup, enhancing your control and stability on the rink.

\nThe professional natural rubber suspensions deliver excellent cushioning, reducing the impact of vibrations and bumps during skating. This feature is essential for maintaining comfort during extended sessions and provides better control over your skates. The professional white metric toe stop (not canted) offers reliable stopping power, crucial for quick stops and precise maneuvers.

column2:
>Roll Line Spacer:

You should always used a spacer between your bearings to have a much better performance.
The Roll line spacer come only in 7mm
column3:
>Why should we use Spacers in Roller Skate Wheels.
Any Wheel with Bearings\, when properly installed on Skate Axles\, should use Spacers.

If you look at the roller skating history years ago\, when we used Jam Nuts instead of the Nylon inserted Lock Nuts used today.
A Jam Nut must be locked down to keep from loosening and coming off.
To achieve good Roll from this type of configuration\, the sides of the spacer must be absolutely parallel\, without any burrs and just
a couple of thousandths of an inch wider than the web (that smaller center portion) of the wheel or space between the Bearings.
The sizes of the web of the Wheels vary between manufacturers and even between various wheels from the same manufacturer\, in some cases.

Many years ago\, the wheel manufacturers used to supply the Spacers with the Wheels.
When the Axle Nut is tightened down on the wheel (with bearings and a spacer)\, it creates a solid boss of material
(the inner race of the inside Bearing\, the Spacer\, and the inner race of the outside Bearing)
that effectively increases the Axle size from 7mm to approximately 14mm.
The increasing of the Axle size greatly reduces the possibility of bending or breaking any Axle.
By locking the Bearings and Spacer down\, it also assures that the center race of each Bearing is not spinning on the Axle\,
but that the balls of the Bearings are actually doing the work that they are intended to.
Tightening the Axle Nut on a Wheel without a Spacer can severely mis-align the center races of the bearings to the outer races
of the Bearings by compressing the inner races towards the center of the Wheel.
The Locked Down approach also requires near perfect alignment of the Wheel bore and the web of the Wheel must have very
clean square corners to provide a seat for the outer race of the Bearings.

Today\, Lock Nuts are accepted\, most Wheel manufacturers do not even supply the Wheel Spacers\, and the tolerances on the width
of the web of the Wheel are not held as tight as they once were.
To my knowledge\, Roll-Line is the only one still making Spacers for Wheels.
They normally come with a complete NEW Frame as an accessory.
Rollerskateusa.com does have spacers available in sets of 8 from Roll-Line.
column4:
>(Just a Note: not every spacer will make every wheel work properly. Sometimes there are spacers that are non-parallel\,
have a burr\, or are just too small to match the web of a specific Wheel.)

The spacers have always been a part that the manufacturing cost must be minimized\, or for some manufacturers\, completely eliminated.
They are made from a long tube that is sawn into the Spacers\, and the tolerances are not usually as rigorously controlled as on other parts
of the Skate. To get the Spacers\, Bearings and Wheels to work\, means sometimes using multiple Spacers to get a specific wheel to roll properly.

When everything goes together well\, there should be little to no variation in the speed of a free spinning Wheel
column5:
>(with the Axle Nut (Lock Nut) is just backed off) and when the Axle Nut (Lock Nut) is tightened down.

To achieve a Free Rolling complete set of Wheels in this manner will take time and patience and plenty of Spacers along with a good Bearing Press
like the our new Roll-Line Bearing Press/Puller.

All Roll-Line Wheels have either a Precision Machined Hub with the Tread adhered to it\, or
the Wheels are Molded with the Precision Center Hub type of configuration.

Roll-Line Truck Matrix Titanium

\nThe Roll-Line Truck Matrix Titanium is designed for skaters who seek top-tier performance and durability. Crafted from high-quality aluminum, these trucks are equipped with 7mm titanium axles, offering an exceptional balance of strength and lightness. Whether you're an advanced skater or a competitive athlete, these trucks are engineered to enhance your skating experience.

\nEach truck assembly includes the axles, pivot pins, and nuts, ensuring a secure and precise fit. The titanium axles provide excellent resilience and reduce the risk of bending or breaking under intense conditions. This makes them ideal for various skating disciplines, including freestyle, dance, and figure skating.

\nUpgrade your skate setup with the Roll-Line Truck Matrix Titanium. These trucks are built to withstand the demands of serious skating, providing stability, control, and long-lasting performance. Please note that the price is per unit, allowing you to purchase the exact number needed for your setup. Experience the superior quality and performance of these premium skate accessories.","

Roll-Line Truck Standard Steel (with 8mm Axles)

\nThe Roll-Line Truck Standard Steel is designed for skaters seeking durability and high performance. Featuring robust aluminum construction paired with 8mm steel axles, these trucks provide exceptional stability and strength for various skating styles. Each unit includes the axle, pivot pin, and nut, ensuring a complete and secure fit for your skates.

\nThese trucks are compatible with several Roll-Line plates, including Variant M, Variant C, Mariner Cup, Mistral, Energy Steel, Giotto, and Spin. This versatility makes them an excellent choice for skaters who require dependable performance across different skating disciplines, whether it's freestyle, dance, or figure skating.

\nEnhance your skating experience with the Roll-Line Truck Standard Steel. Each unit is priced individually, allowing you to purchase the exact number needed for your setup. Trust in Roll-Line's commitment to quality and performance with these reliable skate trucks.","

Roll-Line Truck Standard Steel (with 8mm Axles)

\nThe Roll-Line Truck Standard Steel is an essential upgrade for skaters who demand durability and precision in their equipment. Engineered with high-quality materials, these trucks are designed to enhance your skating experience by providing stability and strength for a variety of skating disciplines.

\nEach truck is constructed from premium aluminum, offering a lightweight yet robust base. The 8mm steel axles are designed for maximum strength and durability, ensuring your skates can handle the rigors of intense use. The combination of aluminum and steel materials results in a sturdy truck that delivers consistent performance and long-lasting reliability.

\nThe Roll-Line Truck Standard Steel comes as a complete assembly, including the 8mm axle, pivot pin, and nut. This ensures a secure and precise fit, allowing you to install the trucks with ease and confidence. The precision engineering of these components guarantees that they fit together perfectly, minimizing any unwanted movement or loosening during use.

\nOne of the standout features of the Roll-Line Truck Standard Steel is its compatibility with a wide range of Roll-Line plates. These trucks are designed to fit the Variant M, Variant C, Mariner Cup, Mistral, Energy Steel, Giotto, and Spin plates. This versatility makes them an ideal choice for skaters who use different plates for various skating disciplines.

\nThese trucks are engineered to provide superior performance, whether you are skating freestyle, dance, or figure. The 8mm steel axles offer excellent resilience, reducing the risk of bending or breaking under high stress. This ensures that your skates remain stable and responsive, allowing you to perform at your best.

\n
  • Compatibility: Fits Variant M, Variant C, Mariner Cup, Mistral, Energy Steel, Giotto, and Spin plates

\nInvesting in the Roll-Line Truck Standard Steel means choosing quality and reliability. These trucks are designed to withstand the demands of serious skating, providing you with the stability and control needed to excel. Whether you are a competitive skater or a recreational enthusiast, these trucks will enhance your performance.

\nUpgrade your skates with the Roll-Line Truck Standard Steel today and experience the difference in quality and performance. Each unit is priced individually, allowing you to purchase exactly what you need for your setup. Trust Roll-Line for superior skate accessories that deliver unmatched durability and precision.

This tool is also often called a centerline tool because its general purpose is to find the center of the boot. Every skater is different and every skater might require something a little different. Tool designed to help those mount skating boots. This tool is the exact tool that we use here in our shop when mounting our skates. Tool is not 100% precise but is used as a guideline when mounting. This tool is also often called a centerline tool because its general purpose is to find the center of the boot. Every skater is different and every skater might require something a little different. Use this tool to find the center of each boot and make your adjustments off that center line. This will ensure that both plates are mounted in the same spot on each boot. ,,,,,,,1251.0,1222.0,1.0,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column5: >Bont Avenger Hardcore 110mm Inline Speed Wheels
column6: >The Avenger Hardcore is the first mass-produced aluminum hub inline racing wheel. We chose aluminum as the hub material because it offers more rebound than plastic or nylon hubs. The Avenger Hardcore 110mm inline speed skating wheel is produced by MPC for Bont and it has recorded the highest ever rebound score of any wheel MPC has ever produced. MPC wheels have won more world titles in the last 10 years than any other wheel manufacturer.
column8: >To ensure the hub is not too stiff we have curved the spokes. CAD-CAM software was used to perfect the weight and rebound of the hub. A mechanical lock is used to ensure the urethane can never be dislodged from the hub. The Avenger has a full 24mm wheel width with a 110mm outer diameter. The bearing bore is machined before and after anodizing to ensure a perfect fit.
column10:
>The urethane is poured by MPC and it uses their patented high rebound flex band.

column1: \nThe Roll-Line Tube Wrench is an essential tool for any skater using Roll-Line plates. Designed to fit 11mm and 17mm nuts, this standard tube wrench is perfect for all Roll-Line plates with 7mm screws. Made from durable materials, it ensures you can easily and efficiently make adjustments and maintain your skates. Whether you're tightening or loosening components, this tube wrench provides the precision and leverage needed for effective skate maintenance.

\nThe compact design makes it easy to carry in your skate bag, so you always have it on hand when you need it. The Roll-Line Tube Wrench is not just a tool, but a necessity for anyone serious about their skating. Ensure your skates are always in top condition with this reliable and easy-to-use wrench.","

Roll-Line Tube Wrench 11mm - 17mm

\nThe Roll-Line Tube Wrench is an indispensable tool designed specifically for maintaining and adjusting Roll-Line skate plates. This standard tube wrench is crafted to fit 11mm and 17mm nuts, making it compatible with all Roll-Line plates that utilize 7mm screws. Whether you're a professional skater or a recreational enthusiast, having the right tools is crucial for ensuring your equipment performs at its best, and the Roll-Line Tube Wrench is exactly what you need.

\nConstructed from high-quality materials, the Roll-Line Tube Wrench is built to last. It can withstand the rigors of regular use, providing you with a reliable tool that won't let you down. The robust design ensures that you can apply the necessary torque without worrying about bending or breaking the wrench.

\nThis wrench is specifically designed to work with all Roll-Line plates that feature 7mm screws. The dual size functionality (11mm and 17mm) makes it versatile and convenient, allowing you to handle multiple adjustments with a single tool. Whether you're tightening your trucks or adjusting your toe stops, this wrench has got you covered.

\nThe Roll-Line Tube Wrench is designed for ease of use. Its ergonomic design provides a comfortable grip, allowing you to work on your skates without straining your hands. The compact size makes it easy to carry, so you can take it with you wherever you go. Whether you're at the rink or out on the streets, you can always have this essential tool on hand.

\nRegular maintenance is key to ensuring the longevity and performance of your skates. With the Roll-Line Tube Wrench, you can easily perform essential tasks such as tightening screws and adjusting components. This helps prevent issues that could affect your skating experience, such as loose trucks or misaligned parts. By keeping your skates in optimal condition, you can enjoy a smoother, safer ride.

\n
  • Compatibility: Works with all Roll-Line plates with 7mm screws

\nInvesting in the right tools is crucial for any skater, and the Roll-Line Tube Wrench is an essential addition to your skate maintenance kit. Its durable construction, perfect fit for Roll-Line plates, and ease of use make it a must-have for anyone serious about skating. Ensure your skates are always in top condition with this reliable and efficient tube wrench. Don't let equipment issues hold you back—keep rolling smoothly with the Roll-Line Tube Wrench 11mm - 17mm.",,,taxable,,1,,,0,0,1.0,9,6.0,2.0,0,,,13.0,"Roller Skates > Roll Line Skates, Roller Skates > Roll Line Skates > Roll Line Tools",,,http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/11mm17mmtubewrench1.jpg,,,,,RollLineToolTubeWrench,,,,0,Roll Line,,,ExtraField 1,Roll-Line Tube Wrench,1.0,0.0,ExtraField 6,"
column4: >Roll Line Standard Tube Wrench:
column8:
>The Roll-Line TUBE WRENCH 11mm – 17mm is used to simply Tighten or Loosen the Action Adjustment on Roll-Line
Click and Non-Click Skate Models\, with the 17mm end of the Tube Wrench to adjust the amount of action desired.
column10:
>Keeping the King Pin Locking Screw Tight is very important to the safety of the Skaters.
The King Pin Locking Screw is also known as the “KEEPER Screw”\, (which loosens with the 4mm Allen Wrench)
as it keeps the Adjustment Nut from being able to be backed off to the point that the skate will come apart\, while skating.
column12:
>If the King Pin Action Adjustment Nut or Click Nuts are loosened (to achieve more flexible Action) to the point that they hit the “Keeper Screw”\,
the Action has been Loosened to the maximum of its adjustment range.
This is based on the Suspensions (Cushions) that you are using.
If you need more Action\, a more flexible Suspension (Cushion) will be required\, to allow the Skate Adjustment to be operated
in the normal operating range of the adjustment.
The Normal Operating Range\, Does NOT include backing out the “KEEPER Screw” to achieve a more Flexible Action.
column17:
